## Project Responsibilities

### 🌐 Web (Presentation Layer)

**Purpose:** Handle HTTP requests, render views, coordinate UI updates via events.

**Folder Structure:**

```
Web/
├─ Controllers/          # Thin controllers (delegate to Application)
│  └─ HomeController.cs
├─ Views/                # Razor views + HTMX partials
│  ├─ Home/
│  │  ├─ Index.cshtml    # Full page
│  │  ├─ _TodoList.cshtml # Partial (HTMX target)
│  │  └─ _TodoItem.cshtml # Item partial
│  └─ Shared/
│     └─ _Layout.cshtml
├─ wwwroot/              # Static assets
│  ├─ css/
│  ├─ js/
│  └─ lib/
├─ Events/               # Event chain registration
│  └─ SwapEventChains.cs
├─ Extensions/           # Service registration
│  └─ ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs
└─ Program.cs            # Startup configuration
```

**Controller Example:**

```csharp
// Web/Controllers/TodosController.cs
public class TodosController : SwapController
{
    private readonly ITodoService _todoService;
    
    public TodosController(ITodoService todoService)
    {
        _todoService = todoService;
    }
    
    [HttpGet]
    public async Task<IActionResult> Index()
    {
        var todos = await _todoService.GetAllTodosAsync();
        return View(todos);
    }
    
    [HttpGet]
    public async Task<IActionResult> List()
    {
        var todos = await _todoService.GetAllTodosAsync();
        return PartialView("_TodoList", todos);
    }
    
    [HttpPost]
    public async Task<IActionResult> Create(string title)
    {
        await _todoService.CreateTodoAsync(title);
        // Service fires domain event → event chain → UI updates
        return Ok();
    }
}
```

**Key Responsibilities:**
- Receive HTTP requests
- Validate input (basic)
- Delegate to Application services
- Return views/partials
- NO direct database access
- NO business logic

