### 🧠 Domain (Core Business)

**Purpose:** Define business entities, domain events, and repository contracts. Pure business logic with zero framework dependencies.

**Folder Structure:**

```
Domain/
├─ Entities/             # Domain models
│  ├─ TodoItem.cs
│  └─ BaseEntity.cs
├─ Events/               # Domain event names
│  └─ DomainEvents.cs
└─ Interfaces/           # Repository contracts
   └─ ITodoRepository.cs
```

**Entity Example:**

```csharp
// Domain/Entities/TodoItem.cs
public class TodoItem
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Title { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public bool IsComplete { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? CompletedAt { get; set; }
    
    // Domain behavior
    public void Complete()
    {
        if (!IsComplete)
        {
            IsComplete = true;
            CompletedAt = DateTime.UtcNow;
        }
    }
    
    public void Uncomplete()
    {
        if (IsComplete)
        {
            IsComplete = false;
            CompletedAt = null;
        }
    }
}
```

**Domain Events:**

```csharp
// Domain/Events/DomainEvents.cs
public static class DomainEvents
{
    public static string TodoCreated => "entity.created:todo";
    public static string TodoUpdated => "entity.updated:todo";
    public static string TodoDeleted => "entity.deleted:todo";
    public static string TodoCompleted => "entity.completed:todo";
}
```

**Repository Contract:**

```csharp
// Domain/Interfaces/ITodoRepository.cs
public interface ITodoRepository
{
    Task<IEnumerable<TodoItem>> GetAllAsync();
    Task<TodoItem?> GetByIdAsync(int id);
    Task AddAsync(TodoItem todo);
    Task UpdateAsync(TodoItem todo);
    Task DeleteAsync(int id);
    Task SaveChangesAsync();
}
```

**Key Responsibilities:**
- Define business entities
- Define domain event names (pure strings)
- Define repository interfaces
- Contain domain behavior (methods like `Complete()`)
- NO dependencies on other layers
- NO infrastructure concerns
- Pure C# classes

