## Event System Flow

### Domain Events → UI Updates

**1. Domain layer defines event names:**

```csharp
// Domain/Events/DomainEvents.cs
public static class DomainEvents
{
    public static string TodoCreated => "entity.created:todo";
}
```

**2. Application layer fires events:**

```csharp
// Application/Services/TodoService.cs
public async Task CreateTodoAsync(string title)
{
    // ... save todo
    _eventBus.Fire(DomainEvents.TodoCreated);
}
```

**3. Web layer maps domain events to UI events:**

```csharp
// Web/Events/SwapEventChains.cs
public static class SwapEventChains
{
    public static void Register(ISwapEvents events)
    {
        events.Chain(
            DomainEvents.TodoCreated,  // Domain event
            "ui.refreshList",           // UI event
            "ui.showToast");            // UI event
    }
}
```

**4. Views listen to UI events:**

```html
<!-- Web/Views/Home/_TodoList.cshtml -->
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Todos/List"
     hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body"
     hx-swap="outerHTML">
    <!-- List content -->
</div>
```

**Flow diagram:**

```
User submits form
        ↓
Controller → Service.CreateTodoAsync()
                    ↓
            Repository.AddAsync()
                    ↓
            _eventBus.Fire("entity.created:todo")
                    ↓
            Event Chain: entity.created:todo → ui.refreshList
                    ↓
            HX-Trigger header sent to browser
                    ↓
            HTMX elements with hx-trigger="ui.refreshList" fire
                    ↓
            Partial views re-fetch and update
```

