## Database Strategy

### Entity Framework Core Configuration

**Connection string:**

```json
// appsettings.json
{
  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "DefaultConnection": "Data Source=app.db"
  }
}
```

**Registration:**

```csharp
// Web/Program.cs
builder.Services.AddDbContext<AppDbContext>(options =>
    options.Use{{DatabaseProvider}}(
        builder.Configuration.GetConnectionString("DefaultConnection")));
```

### Migrations

**Create migration:**

```bash
dotnet ef migrations add MigrationName -p src/Infrastructure -s src/Web
```

**Apply migration:**

```bash
dotnet ef database update -p src/Infrastructure -s src/Web
```

**Generate SQL script:**

```bash
dotnet ef migrations script -p src/Infrastructure -s src/Web --output migration.sql
```

### Auto-Migrations on Startup

Configured in `Program.cs`:

```csharp
if (app.Environment.IsDevelopment())
{
    using var scope = app.Services.CreateScope();
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<AppDbContext>();
    
    try
    {
        db.Database.Migrate();
        await SeedRunner.RunAsync(db, scope.ServiceProvider);
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        var logger = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ILogger<Program>>();
        logger.LogError(ex, "Migration or seeding failed");
    }
}
```

