## Dependency Injection

### Service Registration

```csharp
// Web/Extensions/ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs
public static class ServiceCollectionExtensions
{
    public static IServiceCollection AddApplicationServices(
        this IServiceCollection services)
    {
        // Application services
        services.AddScoped<ITodoService, TodoService>();
        
        // Infrastructure repositories
        services.AddScoped<ITodoRepository, TodoRepository>();
        
        // Event bus adapter
        services.AddScoped<IEventBus, SwapEventBusAdapter>();
        
        return services;
    }
}
```

**Usage in Program.cs:**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddApplicationServices();
```

### Dependency Flow

```
Controller (Web)
    ↓ depends on
ITodoService (Application interface)
    ↓ implemented by
TodoService (Application)
    ↓ depends on
ITodoRepository (Domain interface)
    ↓ implemented by
TodoRepository (Infrastructure)
    ↓ depends on
AppDbContext (Infrastructure)
```

**Benefits:**
- Easy to mock for testing
- Swap implementations without changing dependent code
- Clear dependency direction (always inward toward Domain)

