## Security Considerations

### Input Validation

**Model binding (automatic):**

```csharp
[HttpPost]
public async Task<IActionResult> Create([FromForm] CreateTodoRequest request)
{
    if (!ModelState.IsValid)
        return BadRequest(ModelState);
    
    await _todoService.CreateTodoAsync(request.Title);
    return Ok();
}
```

**Data annotations:**

```csharp
public class CreateTodoRequest
{
    [Required]
    [StringLength(500, MinimumLength = 1)]
    public string Title { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

### SQL Injection Protection

EF Core uses parameterized queries automatically:

```csharp
// Safe - parameterized
var todos = await _context.TodoItems
    .Where(t => t.Title.Contains(searchTerm))
    .ToListAsync();
```

### CSRF Protection

Already enabled via ASP.NET Core:

```html
<form method="post">
    @Html.AntiForgeryToken()
    <!-- CSRF token included -->
</form>
```

### Production Hardening

```csharp
// Program.cs
if (!app.Environment.IsDevelopment())
{
    app.UseHsts();
    app.UseHttpsRedirection();
    
    // Remove dev tools
    // app.MapSwapDevDashboard();
}
```

